sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor U as User / Calling App
  participant C as A2A Client Agent
  participant D as Agent Card Endpoint (.well-known)
  participant S as Remote A2A Server (Agent API)
  participant T as Task Manager
  participant P as Push/Stream Channel
  participant A as Artifact Store

  U->>C: Ask for delegated task
  C->>D: Discover agent card
  D-->>C: AgentCard (+ capabilities/security)
  opt Protected metadata
    C->>S: GetExtendedAgentCard
    S-->>C: Extended card details
  end
  C->>S: SendMessage(message, configuration)

  alt Immediate/short operation
    S-->>C: Message (final)
    C-->>U: Return response
  else Long-running operation
    S->>T: Create task
    S-->>C: Task(submitted/working)

    par Streaming/push updates
      T->>S: Status/message updates
      S->>P: Publish TaskStatusUpdateEvent
      P-->>C: Status/message events (stream/subscription/webhook)
    and Polling fallback (non-streaming clients)
      loop Optional polling
        C->>S: GetTask(taskId)
        S-->>C: Task(current state)
      end
    end

    opt Input required
      T-->>C: Task(input-required + message)
      C->>S: SendMessage (follow-up input)
      S->>T: Resume task
    end

    T->>A: Persist final artifact(s)
    A-->>T: Artifact reference(s)
    T-->>S: Final task result prepared
    S-->>C: Final Task(completed/failed/rejected/canceled) + artifact output
    C-->>U: Deliver final result (artifact/message)
  end

  opt User cancels
    U->>C: Cancel request
    C->>S: CancelTask(taskId)
    S->>T: Transition to canceled (if possible)
    S-->>C: Task(canceled or terminal state)
  end
